core.descr: Enable or disable the captive portal feature on the system.
The additional captive portal authentication server port for HTTP web connection. The HTTP port default is 0 which denotes no specific port and the default port (80) is used.
The additional captive portal authentication server port for secured HTTP web connection. The Secure HTTP port default is 0 which denotes no specific port and the default port (443) is used.
The time interval between statistics reports to the cluster controller.A value of 0 indicates reporting is disabled.The value is represented in seconds.
The length of time to maintain an authentication session from a client.This time is measured from when a client initiates an authentication request.The value is represented in seconds.
The identifier associated with this instance of captive portal.
Captive Portal Config Web ID.
The name, in alpha-numeric characters, assigned to this captive portal configuration.
Enable or disable this instance of captive portal on the system.
The protocol mode to be used.
The type of user verification to perform.
Number of languages configured for given CP configuration.
The group ID for this captive portal user database.A group ID may be assigned for databases which use verification mode LOCAL.

Whether the captive portal should redirect newly authenticated clients to the configured URL. If this mode is disabled, the default locale specific welcome page is used. If enabled, the client is redirected to a configured URL.
The URL to which the newly authenticated client is redirected if cpCaptivePortalURLRedirectMode is enabled.
The session timeout. After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected. If this value is set to 0, no timeout is enforced.This value is represented in seconds.
The idle timeout of the session. After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected. If this value is set to 0, no timeout is enforced.This value is represented in seconds.
The RADIUS authentication server name, in alpha-numeric characters (or dotted IP address), assigned to this captive portal configuration.

The maximum bandwidth up/transmit bytes per second rate of the session.After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected.If this value is set to 0, no rate limiting is enforced.This value is represented in bytes (however; converted and stored as bits/sec).

The maximum bandwidth down/receive bytes per second rate of the session.After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected.If this value is set to 0, no rate limiting is enforced.This value is represented in bytes (however; converted and stored as bits/sec).

The maximum input octets (bytes) allowed for the session.After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected.If this value is set to 0, no rate limiting is enforced.This value is represented in bytes.

The maximum Output octets (bytes) allowed for the session.After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected.If this value is set to 0, no rate limiting is enforced.This value is represented in bytes.

The maximum input/output octets (bytes) allowed for the session.After this limit has been reached the user will be disconnected.If this value is set to 0, no rate limiting is enforced.This value is represented in bytes.
CP Web language code. This is used to identify the choice for customized content. IANA Lang Subtag Code plus the optional region code.
CP Web link language locale. This is the text to display and identify the web locale. This shows in the administration tab and the validation page at the top which provides user selection.
Used with Reset Button. Load with default values.

CP Web message text for no accept failure. This is error text to display when the user attempts to connect but did not check/acknowledge the AUP.
CP Web password label.

CP Web message text for a resource failure. This is error text to display when the user attempts to connect but the system has resource problems. This could be such that the CP connection limit has been reached. But this message should be a generic resource failure message.

CP Web message text for a timeout failure. This is error text to display when the user attempts to connect but the connnection has timed out. This could be such that the CP connection time has been reached. Maybe the RADIUS sever is busy. But this message should be a generic timeout failure message.
CP Web title text used to greet the user.
CP Web user (uid) label.
CP Web message text for the welcome page. This is the general text used to notify that the user has successfully connected in the network.
CP Web message title text for the welcome page. This is the title text used in the welcome page once the user is connected. The welcome page is optional.
CP Web message text for WIP. This text is used to indicate to the user work-in-progress (wip) status.
